# Ignore list for the CI link checker (lychee) - one regex per line.
# Add edge cases here rather than weakening real links.

# Placeholder / non-resolvable hosts used inside examples.
^https?://(www\.)?example\.(org|com)(/|$)
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1

# Transient OpenSemanticLab demo/query API endpoints that appear as example
# data (e.g. in the generated legacy keyword inventory), not documentation links.
open-semantic-lab\.org/api/

# The WoT "JSON Schema in RDF" note exists but content-negotiates to HTTP 300
# (Multiple Choices), which the checker rejects; the resource is reachable.
^https://www\.w3\.org/2019/wot/json-schema$

# The spec sections (spec/sections/*.md) are rendered into docs/spec/index.html
# and served at /<version>/spec/, so their site-relative links (../meta/...,
# ../migration/...) are written for the deployed layout, not the source tree.
# A source-based checker resolves them under spec/ and cannot find them; the
# deployed links are correct and the rendered spec's anchors are covered by
# scripts/check_spec.py.
/spec/meta/oold-ui-meta-schema\.json$
/spec/migration/from-legacy-osw/?$
/spec/use-cases/?$
